Cellular Automata, a computational paradigm of Scientific Computing, are pa=
rallel computing models and discrete dynamical systems, utilized for modeli=
ng and simulating complex systems whose evolution can be described in terms=
 of local interactions. Following the success of our first two Cellular Aut=
omata, Theory and Applications Workshop (in 2009 and 2010), which included =
exciting keynotes addressed from a leading Cellular Automata researcher, Pr=
of. Dr. Peter Sloot, and by Prof. Yaroslav D. Sergeyev, father of the Infin=
ity Computer, we are glad to invite you to our third edition.
