ss in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, and Applied Computing (WORLDC=
OMP'11), is to offer scientists, researchers and engineers an opportunity t=
o express and confront their views on trends, challenges, and state-of-the =
art in both theory and diverse application fields such as engineering, phys=
ics, chemistry, biology, geology, medicine, ecology, sociology, traffic con=
trol, economy, etc.
 =

